    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Just to elaborate, it is a \"slashable offense\" to produce two different attestations in the same epoch ([reference](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/core/0_beacon-chain.md#is_slashable_attestation_data)).\r\n\r\nIf a validator _thinks_ there are 4 slots per epoch, but there are _actually_ 8 slots per epoch, then a vote for slots `0, 4` would be _actually_ slashable, but the validator would not think so.",
